fields.description:
When a user tried to remove a site admin which is also an organization admin from the instance. The admin hub error message doesn't helpful and shows a very generic error such as the attachment below:

 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 

Would be helpful for the user to identify the issue if the error message is shows as:

{code}
{"message":"Cannot remove an org admin from the site-admins group"{code}

It would be nice if the AWS zone of the Cloud instance is displayed somewhere within the UI to indicate where the instance is being hosted.

*Workaround:*

# Get the IP address of your Cloud site by running the name server lookup command.
{noformat}
nslookup hostname.atlassian.net
{noformat}
# Download the latest CDIR blocks for AWS. 
{noformat}
wget https://ip-ranges.amazonaws.com/ip-ranges.json
{noformat}
# Check the AWS zone details by looking for first two octanes from the IP address of your Cloud site. e.g, If your IP address is 13.236.8.138, then search for 12.236 in 'ip-ranges.json' file.
{noformat}
cat ip-ranges.json|jq -r '.prefixes[]|[.ip_prefix,.region,.service]|@tsv'|grep 13.236
{noformat}
# Check the exact region name in [AWS Regions and Availability Zones|https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonRDS/latest/UserGuide/Concepts.RegionsAndAvailabilityZones.html ] page. 
e.g., *ap-southeast-2* region name is 'Asia Pacific (Sydney)'
